observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:
Direct the MAcco to make proper disclosures of the unexpended balance of the LDRRMF under the account TL-DRRMF in the Notes to FS in accordance with COA Circular No. 2012-002;
Require the MAcco to verify the discrepancy noted in the Notes to FS and FUR of DRRMF and make/record thenecessaryadjustments in conformity to COA Circular 2012-002;
Enjoin the concerned officials to strictly comply with the reportorial requirements laid out in COACirculars 2012-002 and 2014-002 to have a more reliable and accurate as well as proper monitoring of the 5% LDRRM Fund; and
Strictlyandprudentlycomplywithalltherulesandregulationslaidout relative to LDRRM Fund.

We recommended the following:
The MAcco shall cause the timely preparation and submission of BRSs as required by COA Circular No. 96-011;
The MAcco prepare the necessary journal entries to adjust all reconciling items/discrepancies noted herein. Moreover, we recommended the regular adjustment of reconciling items identified to accurately present the LGU’s actual cash position for each period;
The MT duly prepare the RCI with all its supporting documents and submit the same to the Municipal Accounting Office;
The MT must maintain a cashbook and update it regularly as prescribed by the Manual on the NGAS for LGUs, and thereafter, reconcile her cash book records with the accounting ledgers;
The MAcco together with the MT and Municipal Budget Officer (MBO) must reconcile their records and the above-noted variances in the 20% DF and 5%LDRRMF appearing in the FS and SCBAA, and thereafter, undertake the same regularly; and
Cash accounts must be monitored by key heads of offices consistently and should be presented fairly in accordance with IPSAS 1 and other accounting rules and regulations.

We recommended that:
1. the Municipal Health Officer, together with all other requisitioning department heads, properly accomplish all the required information in the PR, RIS and IAR;
2. the Bids and Awards Committee, through its Chair and Secretariat, ensure that the required information including the terms and conditions in the RFQs and POs are properly filled out to establish and define the obligations of the supplier;
3.  the Municipal Budget Officer to prepare the OBR prior to the issuance of check even in transactions involving cash advances;
4. the Municipal Treasurer to stop the practice of payment of procured goods and services through cash advance of employees and the signing of checks without the duly approved DV and its required attachments. Moreover, ensure that all information are provided in the IAR and RIS in view of the supply and property management function of the Municipal Treasurer; and
5. the Municipal Accountant to always exercise its pre-audit functions and ensure that all supporting documents identified by laws, rules, and regulations for each transaction are complete before certifying completeness of supporting documents in the disbursement vouchers.

1. for the Accounting Office to strictly comply with the timeliness on the recording and submission of accounts as required under existing laws and regulations;

2. for the Treasury Office to hasten/fast tract the transmittal of all documents and reports to the Accounting Office within the most reasonable time to ensure that the latter could comply with regulation.

3. for Management to consider the possibility of augmenting the personnel of the Accounting and Treasury Offices from other departments, especially during the preparation of reports or allow overtime, provided that there are available funds to support the endeavor.
